0.user_question: Mike made 69 dollars mowing lawns over the summer. If he spent 24 dollars buying new mower blades, how many 5 dollar games could he buy with the money he had left?

ost_step.1: Calculate the amount of money Mike has left after buying new mower blades. Mike started with $69 and spent $24 on new mower blades.
ost_step.2: Subtract the cost of the new mower blades from the original amount. Mike has $69 - $24 = $45 left.
ost_step.3: Determine how many $5 games Mike can buy with his remaining money. To do this divide the amount of money Mike has left ($45) by the cost per game ($5).
ost_step.4: Perform the division. Mike can buy $45 / $5 = 9 games with the money he has left.
